Howto use docker image
======================
#Install docker, launch deamon localy
....
#Go to ssabook/ and launch docker by mounting $(pwd) to /host
docker run -t -i -v $(pwd):/host frastell/ubuntu-texlive
#Compile inside docker
cd /host/book
pdflatex book
...
#Edit outside of docker (using another terminal) or install vim in docker
apt-get install vim
...
#If you stopped docker your container might still be present. You can relaunch the last one as follow:
docker start -a -i `docker ps -q -l`
#If you want the container to be removed once you exit (don't care about history and dont want pending docker containers) use --rm when launching
docker run --rm -t -i -v $(pwd):/host frastell/ubuntu-texlive


What I did to create docker image:
=================================
#launched docker from fresh ubuntu latest image
docker run -t -i -v $(pwd):/host ubuntu bash
#installed everything necessary to compile ssabook
apt-get update
apt-get install ...
#exit docker, grab container id, and commit to an image called ubuntu-texlive that we save localy
sudo docker ps -l
sudo docker commit <cont_id> ubuntu-texlive
docker save ubuntu-texlive > ubuntu-texlive.dockerimage 
#create an account (frastell for me) on hub.docker.com
#login to hub.docker.com and create a repository: ubuntu-texlive
#grab image id and tag it
docker images
docker tag <imag_id> frastell/ubuntu-texlive
#log in and push
docker login
docker push frastell/ubuntu-texlive

What to do to make changes to the image
=======================================
docker run -t -i -v $(pwd):/host frastell/ubuntu-texlive bash
apt-get ...
#exit docker, grab container id, and commit to an image called ubuntu-texlive that we save localy
sudo docker ps -l
sudo docker commit <cont_id> ubuntu-texlive
#grab image id and tag it
docker images
docker tag <imag_id> frastell/ubuntu-texlive
#log in and push
docker login
docker push frastell/ubuntu-texlive


